&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 3 Admin Support&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;37.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fixed Term Contract for 6 months.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Monday to Friday 8am-5pm&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic and self-motivated individual to undertake the role of admin support to the Community Paediatrics and Looked After Children&#39;s Services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will provide comprehensive administrative support in the Community Health and Wellbeing Directorate. Primary duties will include; booking appointments, copy typing, dealing with queries from consultants and taking incoming phone calls.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Combining high standards and commitment with experience and excellent communication both written and verbal alongside having exceptional organisational skills are essential for this post. You must be able to provide evidence of working in a busy environment, utilising secretarial and administrative skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will have an excellent knowledge in the use of a variety of databases including Excel and PowerPoint etc. and ideally some internal systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working in a fast paced environment, &amp; therefore require the ability to multitask and priorities your own workload and that of others, work as part of a team and have a professional attitude. The successful candidate must be able to build effective working relationships, with a professional, confident and mature attitude. The successful candidate must be flexible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sophie Hemmings - Admin Team Coordinator&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sophie.Hemmings@covwarkpt.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
